# SASS Installation Steps

## Directory Setup
1. Navigate to alx-intermediate-frontend repository
2. Create new directory: mkdir 0x03-sass_scss
3. Navigate into the directory: cd 0x03-sass_scss

## Node.js Installation (Ubuntu/Linux)
1. Install Node Version Manager (nvm):
   curl -o- https://raw.githubusercontent.com/nvm-sh/nvm/v0.39.7/install.sh | bash

2. Exit terminal and reopen it to load nvm

3. Install Node.js version 20.16:
   nvm install 20.16
   nvm use 20.16

## SASS Installation
1. Install Sass globally using npm:
   npm install -g sass

   OR

   Install specific version (if needed):
   npm install sass@3.7.4

2. Verify installation:
   sass --version

## Alternative Installation Methods
- Using npm locally in project: npm install sass
- Using Yarn: yarn add sass
- Using Homebrew (macOS): brew install sass/sass/sass
- Using Chocolatey (Windows): choco install sass

## Verification
- Check if sass command works: sass --help
- Test compilation: sass input.scss output.css

@debug "Hello world";
